  "texts": [
    "While Learning Analytics shares commonalities with Educational Data Mining (EDM) in terms of objectives, methodologies, and interests, significant differences persist [57].",
    "EDM applies data mining techniques to educational data, aiming to analyze, discover patterns, personalize learning, and improve outcomes [57].",
    "Learning Analytics primarily employs statistics, visualization, discourse analysis, social network analysis, and sense-making models, whereas EDM relies on algorithms such as clustering, classification, Bayesian modeling, relationship mining, and model-based discovery [41,58].",
    "Another notable contrast lies in their emphasis: Learning Analytics focuses on presenting data and results, while EDM prioritizes discussing and comparing Data Mining technology.The integration of AI competencies in education assumes a pivotal role in equipping the future workforce with AI readiness [7].",
    "AI tools have emerged as indispensable assets in the ongoing battle against COVID-19, impacting individuals and industries alike [59]."
